Fix semconv schema URL conflict with otel SDK v1.43.0.

The otel SDK v1.43.0 aligns with semconv v1.40.0, but alertmanager
imports semconv v1.39.0. When both are used in resource.New(), the
conflicting schema URLs cause resource detection to fail. Update the
import to match the SDK's semconv version.

diff --git a/tracing/tracing.go b/tracing/tracing.go
--- a/tracing/tracing.go
+++ b/tracing/tracing.go
@@ -31,7 +31,7 @@ import (
 	"go.opentelemetry.io/otel/propagation"
 	"go.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk/resource"
 	tracesdk "go.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk/trace"
-	semconv "go.opentelemetry.io/otel/semconv/v1.39.0"
+	semconv "go.opentelemetry.io/otel/semconv/v1.40.0"
 	"go.opentelemetry.io/otel/trace"
 	"go.opentelemetry.io/otel/trace/noop"
 	"google.golang.org/grpc/credentials"
